President Joseph R. Biden has proclaimed May 1, 2022, as Loyalty Day in the United States. On this day, Americans are encouraged to reaffirm their commitment to the nation and its principles of freedom, justice, equality, and dignity. The unity and common purpose of Americans, despite their differences, has been the driving force behind the country's success. While acknowledging that the nation has not always fully lived up to its promise of equality and justice for all, the proclamation emphasizes the importance of working together to form a more perfect union. The contributions of veterans, activists, workers, entrepreneurs, educators, first responders, and essential workers are recognized and appreciated. Loyalty Day is an opportunity to celebrate the shared American spirit and honor those who have defended freedom and ideals. The proclamation calls upon the people of the United States to observe this day by displaying the American flag and pledging allegiance to the Republic.